race.description: Matko Hire Goodbye Albany, Farewell Aus Handicap
race.comment: DARKBONEE (12) resumes off two close-up placings in better city class. The promising galloper just missed here on debut on a soft track and has won two jumpouts in preparation for this. Rates tough to beat. DIDN'T MISS MANY (10) also has the ability and went close in a Bendigo 70 before the spell at a mile. Resumed on a deep track at Pakenham and will be much sharper today. Proven second-up and the blinkers go on again. WOLF TWENTY ONE (8) is also lightly raced and is heading in the right direction. Won a 62 here two back and held that number with a solid placing at Caulfield Heath. Peaks and maps to get every chance. CACHINK (6) resumes and performs fresh. He's raced well in decent metro races and he won a recent jumpout with race ride Yendall aboard. Gets the blinkers again and is likely to be further improved. MERE MORSEL (3) is one to include at a price. Races forward and his win this grade at Dunkeld has him in the mix.
